<br>
&quot;Guild Rules And Conduct<br>
The following rules have been established to make our playing time more enjoyable and not as a means to take away from an individual&amp;#146;s total gaming experience. <br>
<br>
1) Conduct and Character Issues: <br>
<br>
With regard to conduct and attitudes, we encourage people to have fun, laugh and enjoy each other&amp;#146;s company. Do not participate in offensive behavior that may be degrading to other members or even yourself. Please try to police your own actions or they may be reviewed for guild disciplinary actions by our officers. <br>
<br>
Some of the more serious offenses are kill stealing, deliberate deception and any attempt to defraud guild members as well as other players. Our guild members should adhere to the General Guidelines as indicated by Verant. Lying, undermining other members, begging or leaving your wiped out group without offering to help are examples of conduct we wish not have associated with At Deaths Door. When in doubt about a conduct issue, contact a guild officer for advice - &quot;Ignorance&quot; is not a viable excuse. <br>
<br>
Its every guild members duty to act as a guild custodian and police not only your own, but others actions of guild members. Please be discreet when handling these situations and not openly berate members in an open guild chat forum unless no other recourse is available. <br>
<br>
Use common sense when dealing with problems with guildmates and others. Try to solve any problems that you may encounter on your own at first. If you cannot, then please get an officer involved before making snap decisions. Disbanding from the guild &amp;#147;in the heat of the moment&amp;#148; is frowned upon and likely you will not get a re-invite. Disbanding from the guild will result in the loss of all GPK points. <br>
<br>
At Death&amp;#146;s Door does not condone a player having characters in a variety of guilds and require that all characters are associated with this guild.&quot;<br>
<br>
******<br>
<br>
I too feel sorry that this happened, for Maeve and also for my former guildmates who joined ADD and are now caught in the middle. I have had only one issue with one member of ADD personally, and to me, it did not reflect on the guild. To me, the character and reputation of Radiant and those members I value highly, and for them to blast ADD for wrongdoing says something to me...<br>
<br>
it happened...<br>
<br>
I had heard about the Rage thing the other morning, as I logged on just after Rage went down at 5am. I was surprised there wasn't a flame about it, since Rage is a favorite topic of conversation on the boards. But I know there wasn't one... Radiant has class, and respect for others. For there to be an all out explosion towards ADD and Maeve actually flaming (nice one by the way), there is a reason. <br>
<br>
I am unsure why the cleric in ADD has had such trouble with getting Rage. If it's true that he is left to camp there for days on end alone, that is most likely the reason. Camping Ragefire requires support from the whole guild, and if ADD, with their numbers and strength would put even half of their guild to camp with him, he would get it in no time. <br>
<br>
I am sad to see such things going on, and it's too bad with all the zones in Norrath and on the moon, there are still issues with people taking advantage of someone else's hard work, instead of going elsewhere to make their own successes.<br>
